> Our Root Vegetable Stew and Cheesy Ciabatta is a delicious veggie option that makes it
> easy to eat more veg in your diet and try something new!

Trim the @parsnip{1} and @carrot{1} (no need to peel), then slice both into rounds about 1cm thick.
Quarter the @closed cup mushrooms{225%g}. Chop the @baking potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).
Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat.
Once hot, add the potatoes, carrot, parsnip and mushrooms. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then stir-fry until slightly tender and browned, ~{8-10%minutes}.
Meanwhile, boil a full #kettle{}.

Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{90%g}(grated). Halve the @ciabatta{2} and lay onto a #baking tray{}, cut-side up.
In a #measuring jug{}, whisk together the @plain flour{1%tbsp}, @red wine stock paste{28%g} and @vegetable stock paste{15%g}. Slowly whisk in the @boiling water{500%ml} until smooth.

Add the @tomato puree{30%g}, @dried rosemary{1%sprig} and the garlic to the veg and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.
Slowly stir the stock mixture into the veg until incorporated. Bring the stew up to the boil whilst stirring, then reduce the heat to medium and simmer until the veg is tender and the stew has thickened, ~{12-14%minutes}.
Season with salt, pepper and @sugar{½%tsp}. Add a splash of water if needed.

While the stew simmers, preheat your #grill{} to high.
Lay the ciabatta onto a baking tray, cut-side up. Spread over the remaining garlic and drizzle with a little @olive oil{}.
Top with the grated Cheddar and season with pepper.
Grill the bread on the top shelf of your #oven{} until golden, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Share the root vegetable stew between your #bowls{}.
Serve the cheesy bread alongside.
Enjoy!